<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-1.01</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 1.01 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>MICROSOFT CORPORATION </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>CONFLICT MINERALS
REPORT </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>FOR THE REPORTING PERIOD FROM </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>JANUARY&nbsp;1 TO DECEMBER&nbsp;31, 2017 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>I.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>INTRODUCTION </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This Conflict Minerals Report (&#147;CMR&#148;) for MICROSOFT CORPORATION (&#147;Microsoft&#148;) is
filed as an exhibit to Microsoft&#146;s Form SD pursuant to Rule <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">13p-1</FONT> under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#147;Rule&#148;) for the 2017 reporting year. The report covers all Microsoft
majority-owned subsidiaries and variable interest entities that are subject to the Rule. The Rule imposes certain due diligence and reporting obligations on US Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) registrants whose manufactured
products (including products contracted to be made for each registrant) contain &#147;conflict minerals&#148; necessary to the functionality or production of those products. The Rule defines &#147;conflict minerals&#148; to include cassiterite,
columbite-tantalite, gold, wolframite and their derivatives limited to tin, tantalum, tungsten, and gold (collectively referred to as &#147;3TGs&#148;). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft
develops, licenses, and supports a wide range of software products, services, and hardware devices that deliver new opportunities, greater convenience, and enhanced value to people&#146;s lives. Microsoft is committed to the responsible sourcing of
raw materials globally in support of human rights, labor, health and safety, environmental protection, and business ethics. Our commitment and strategy are outlined in Microsoft&#146;s <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Responsible
Sourcing of Raw Materials</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;RSRM&#148;) policy. Under our policy, Microsoft takes a holistic approach to the responsible sourcing of raw materials while working toward the use of conflict-free minerals
in our devices. We strive to avoid harming communities through an inadvertent <I>de facto</I> embargo of minerals from the Democratic Republic of the Congo (&#147;DRC&#148;) or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">DRC-adjoining</FONT> countries. The
Rule defines the DRC and any of its adjoining countries as a &#147;Covered Country.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This CMR demonstrates progress for the 2017 reporting year. The
number of <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Responsible Minerals Assurance Process</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;RMAP&#148;) <SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP>, formerly Conflict-Free Smelter
Program (&#147;CFSP&#148;), conformant smelters or refiners (&#147;SORs&#148;) in our supply chain increased<B> </B>from 249 to 253. Since our last CMR filing, we have taken the following actions to improve our raw material due diligence:
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Full integration of the RSRM program into our Social and Environmental Accountability (&#147;SEA&#148;) audit process through the full use of Microsoft&#146;s Audit Management System; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Publicized Microsoft&#146;s SEA supplier manual, which includes Responsible Sourcing of Raw Material Requirements, to increase transparency of the program; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Strengthened external partnerships to increase <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">on-the-ground</FONT></FONT> risk mitigation and enhance Microsoft&#146;s due diligence capabilities; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>Please note: this CMR contains references and hyper-text links to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-Microsoft,</FONT> external websites. These links are provided
for informational purposes only. Their inclusion in this CMR does not establish Microsoft&#146;s endorsement of assumption of liability for content posted on these external websites. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">1 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Strengthened internal partnerships to identify raw material risk at an early product development stage. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft
devices contain one or more 3TGs and are within the Rule&#146;s scope. Devices manufactured during the 2017 reporting year included: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Surface line of computers and other intelligent devices; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Xbox gaming/entertainment consoles and accessories; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Hololens, which is the first self-contained holographic computer; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Personal computing accessories (mice, headsets, and keyboards). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On the basis of our &#147;Reasonable Country of Origin
Inquiry&#148; (&#147;RCOI&#148;) (see Section II), we determined that 3TGs contained in our devices may have originated in a Covered Country. Therefore, we are submitting this CMR, which describes the conflict minerals due diligence we performed
during the 2017 reporting year, as an exhibit to our Form SD. We have published the CMR externally on our <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>responsible sourcing website</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL">. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The manufacture of devices during any specified time period may include raw materials sourced before, as well as during, that time period. In particular, some 3TGs used
during the 2017 reporting year may have been smelted and refined prior to the Rule&#146;s initial reporting period. While such 3TGs are excluded from the Rule&#146;s scope, our RCOI and supply chain due diligence conducted for the 2017 reporting
year may have included such minerals. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>II.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>REASONABLE COUNTRY OF ORIGIN INQUIRY </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our RCOI corresponds to the first and second steps of the five-step <FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>OECD Due Guidance for Responsible Supply Chains of Minerals from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;OECD Guidance&#148;). The OECD Guidance provides a
framework for detailed due diligence to support responsible global supply chain management of minerals and is currently the only internationally recognized framework for raw material due diligence. The OECD Guidance (including its Supplements)
applies to each of the 3TGs and to Microsoft as a &#147;downstream company.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft does not source directly from 3TG raw material providers. We
source products from suppliers, which source materials, components, and products from their <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers. Our supply chain is extensive and complex with many layers of suppliers positioned between
ourselves and 3TG raw materials providers and processors (also known as &#147;SORs&#148;). We refer collectively in this CMR to directly contracted strategic suppliers as <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;in-scope</FONT> suppliers.&#148; Due to
our extended supply chain, we leverage our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to provide information on the sources and chains of custody of 3TGs necessary to the manufacture of our devices. We provide more detail on our
supply chain due diligence process in Section III. The graphic below demonstrates Microsoft&#146;s span of influence with its suppliers. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">2 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g594033st006.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Establish Strong Company Management Systems </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>1.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Company Policies </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Microsoft Global Human Rights
Statement</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> and </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Supplier Code of Conduct</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> define our expectations concerning ethical business, employment,
environmental, and worker safety practices. Microsoft&#146;s RSRM policy describes our commitment and strategy to responsibly source raw materials used in our devices. Microsoft is committed to indirectly source raw materials in support of human
rights, labor, health and safety, environment, and ethics. This pledge extends to the harvesting, extraction, and transportation of raw materials globally and to all substances used in our devices&#151;unbounded by specific materials or locations.
Our policy supports implementation of programs that are region-specific and work toward the use of conflict-free minerals in our devices. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We require our
suppliers to conform to these policies and to include them in their contracts with their <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers. Our supplier specifications and internal procedures establish supplier requirements for the
responsible sourcing of raw materials, including 3TGs. We audit our suppliers to ensure these requirements are met. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>2.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Internal Management Team </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">A cross-functional team supports Microsoft&#146;s responsible sourcing and 3TG
compliance activities. The General Manager of the Devices Group sponsors the team. The team consists of representatives from Sourcing; Social and Environmental Accountability; Manufacturing; Accounting/Finance; Internal Audit; Experiences and
Devices Group; Corporate, External and Legal Affairs; Business and Corporate Responsibility; Information Services; and Product Environmental Compliance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This team
meets quarterly to assess the program&#146;s progress, identify steps necessary to meet our compliance obligations, and identify areas for continuous improvement. The team also trains other internal stakeholders on their roles and responsibilities
for implementing and supporting Microsoft&#146;s responsible sourcing program. Related procedures are documented in our internal Responsible Sourcing Program Manual. Team members are responsible for developing, reviewing, filing, and publishing the
CMR. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">3 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>3.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>System of Supply Chain Controls and Transparency </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our suppliers provide us with information concerning the source
and chain of custody of raw materials from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas (&#147;CAHRAs&#148;), including 3TGs, contained in the products and components they supply to us. Many of our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers
are also subject to the Rule. These suppliers rely on information provided by their suppliers to meet their compliance obligations. Our contracts require all Microsoft <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to identify by weight
each and every substance contained in the materials, components, and products supplied to us, including 3TGs. Our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers are responsible for communicating our sourcing requirements and
specifications to their <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers, including our raw material due diligence requirements. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, we require
all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to submit a Conflict Minerals Reporting Template (&#147;CMRT&#148;) annually. These CMRTs are evaluated for completeness, data integrity, due diligence thoroughness, and sourcing risk.
Potential risks may include a failure to fully complete the CMRT, data inconsistencies, and possible sourcing from a CAHRA. Microsoft investigates each identified issue and engages with those suppliers to address all concerns regarding conformance
to Microsoft policies, procedures, and specifications. In cases where the supplier is identified as sourcing from a CAHRA, suppliers are required to submit a CMRT more frequently and further assess and mitigate risk with their <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If we find that a supplier has introduced unmitigated risk to the Microsoft supply chain, such as using an
upstream SOR that does not conform to Microsoft&#146;s RSRM policy or specifications, Microsoft requires corrective action to address the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-conformance.</FONT> The response time for corrective action is calibrated
to the severity of the identified risk. Risks are mitigated by supplier engagement, corrective actions, training, and/or additional audits. These controls and related documentation are detailed in
<FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>H02050 - Microsoft Supplier Social and Environmental Accountability Manual</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> and Microsoft internal operating procedures. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft works with impacted suppliers to find sources for RMAP conformant minerals. If a supplier does not commit to a RMAP conformant source within a reasonable time
period, Microsoft places the supplier on restricted status with no new Microsoft business awarded until the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-conformance</FONT> is resolved. Microsoft may also terminate its business relationship with the
supplier. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft is a long-standing member of the <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Responsible Business Alliance</U></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;RBA,&#148; formerly the Electronics Industry Citizenship Coalition or &#147;EICC&#148;). The RBA initiated the CFSP in 2008, which became the RMAP in 2017. The RMAP is one of the most utilized and respected
resources for addressing supply chain responsible sourcing issues. The RMAP uses an independent third-party audit to assess and monitor whether SORs process 3TGs from sources that directly or indirectly finance or benefit armed groups in a Covered
Country. Microsoft funded an early adopters program to subsidize audit costs, enabling more SORs to be audited. Microsoft also financially supports the </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Industrial Technology Research
Institute&#146;s Tin Supply Chain Initiative</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;iTSCi&#148;), which has established a system of traceability and due diligence in Covered Countries. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft works to positively impact <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">end-to-end</FONT></FONT> mining sustainability, from artisanal
mines to larger mining enterprises. Through partnership with the electronics and mining sectors and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">not-for-profit</FONT></FONT> partners, we aspire to improve conditions directly at
the source across a broad scope of issues. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">4 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft supports and participates in numerous partnerships that work to establish responsible mining standards and the
responsible sourcing of minerals. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We partner closely with Pact, the <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Initiative for Responsible Mining
Assurance</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;IRMA&#148;), and </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Alliance for Responsible Mining</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> (&#147;ARM&#148;). These organizations
address human rights concerns in mining and leverage data and technology to bring about even greater change. Empowered by digital technology, Microsoft and our partners are working to drive transformations in the mining sector by addressing issues
of increased scope and complexity. We believe this integrated approach improves conditions for the people working in raw material supply chains. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our primary
relationships are further described below: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Pact: Since 2014, we have supported a Pact project in the DRC to reduce child labor in mining. The results in Pact&#146;s Watoto Inje Ya Mungoti (Children Out of Mining) project verify the effectiveness of Pact&#146;s
approach, data, and experience. The <FONT COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Children Out of Mining</U></FONT> report states: This project &#147;reached 4,100 beneficiaries, of whom 1,881 were children. Bans on child labor were enforced at 23 mine sites in the
target area by the end of the project. Reduction in child labor between 77&nbsp;percent and 97&nbsp;percent over the course of the project to date.&#148; Yves Bawa, Pact country director for DRC, Rwanda, and Burundi notes that, &#147;Microsoft was
one of our first partners on this important issue. Its seed funding helped us achieve groundbreaking progress in the first two years of work.&#148; We recently announced a new, expanded commitment to continue this work over the next three years, as
it is evident that this proven strategy can improve the livelihood of already impoverished workers in artisanal cobalt mines. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Initiative for Responsible Mining Assurance (&#147;IRMA&#148;): IRMA established a multi-stakeholder and independently verifiable responsible mining assurance system that improves social and environmental performance
through the development of global mining standards for large- scale mines. Our partnership involves more than just participation &#150; we are bringing technology to help scope, scale, and implement effective programs. Microsoft recently donated a
technology platform to IRMA that will allow the organization to better implement these assurance standards. By pairing the technology platform with Power BI, a cloud-based business analytics service, stakeholders will be able to track mining
performance against the assurance standards. This real-time information, presented in an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">easy-to-see</FONT></FONT> and
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">easy-to-use</FONT></FONT> interface, will help mining companies and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Governmental</FONT> Organizations (&#147;NGOs&#148;) overcome the inherent
difficulties of scope and complexity of these programs to create new insights and inspire additional progress. With learnings from this engagement, we hope to enable additional NGO partners to expand their work to create sustainable mining
communities. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">5 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Alliance for Responsible Mining (&#147;ARM&#148;): ARM sets standards for responsible artisanal and small-scale mining and supports and creates opportunities for gold miners, providing them with incentives to become
responsible economic, technological, and environmental enterprises. Seed funding from Microsoft helped ARM secure further resources to develop a Market Entry Standard for Artisanal and Small-scale Gold Miners. In FY18, Microsoft also supported an
ASM gold mining project in Peru. This project was leveraged to attract additional donors to further scale ARM&#146;s efforts to develop certified gold mining sites throughout the region. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>4.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Supplier Engagement </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Given the complexities of the global mineral supply chain, we work closely with our suppliers
around the world to ensure they share our commitment and reflect it in their own programs. RMAP&#146;s &#147;<FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Practical Guidance for Downstream
Companies</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL">&#148; states that &#147;all of the [OECD Guidance&#146;s] red flag triggers are contained in the upstream portion of the supply chain (e.g., SORs and mine of origin).&#148; Because these conflict
mineral supply chain &#147;triggers&#148; are directed to upstream companies, rather than downstream manufacturers such as Microsoft, we mitigate raw material sourcing risks by working with our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT>
suppliers to identify raw material SORs and encourage those facilities to become RMAP conformant or, failing to do so, use an alternate facility that is RMAP conformant. We also participate in industry-wide initiatives that assess SOR conformance
with the OECD Guidance as recommended by RMAP guidance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We drive responsible sourcing through our extended supply chain by surveying our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers&#146; sourcing of raw materials in their upstream supply chains. We also use tools that include supplier and smelter capability building and support broader industry efforts to promote responsible
mining and sourcing. Finally, we conduct audits of our contracted suppliers to verify conformance to Microsoft requirements. More information is set forth below. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Supplier Requirements</U>: We require our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to meet our material disclosure requirements and related responsible sourcing policies through contractual
provisions and product specifications. We communicate, monitor, and track supplier adherance to ensure conformance through the Microsoft Audit Management System (&#147;AMS&#148;). These policies and procedures are outlined in Section III and can be
accessed publically on our <FONT COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Responsible Sourcing Website</U></FONT>. We also train our directly contracted suppliers to meet our requirements through classes, educational forums, and direct communications. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Capability Building and Partnerships</U>: We work closely with our supply chain partners to build the raw material supplier capabilities for achieving our responsible sourcing goals. With the empowerment of digital
technology, Microsoft and our partners can drive transformations in the mining sector by addressing issues of increased scope and complexity. We invest in industry programs, such as the RMAP, to increase suppliers&#146; capabilities and provide them
with platforms to share best practices. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt"><U>Supplier Audits</U>: Microsoft conducts audits of its directly contracted suppliers to assess their conformance to
Microsoft requirements. All new contracted <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers undergo an Initial Capability Assessment (&#147;ICA&#148;) to verify conformance. Existing contracted
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers also undergo a Sustaining Maintenance Audit (&#147;SMA&#148;) on an annual, biannual, or </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">6 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
triannual basis depending on their risk level. Suppliers must establish and maintain a corporate policy and effective procedures for the responsible sourcing of raw materials. Microsoft selects
and retains only those business partners committed to meeting these requirements. A failure by a supplier or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> supplier to conform to these requirements may constitute a breach of the supplier&#146;s
contractual agreement with Microsoft. During the 2017 reporting year, Microsoft-engaged auditors conducted 174 ICAs and SMAs of approximately 433 directly contracted hardware and packaging suppliers to assess areas of SEA conformance. These ICAs and
SMAs addressed whether the suppliers had a conflict minerals policy, systems in place to implement that policy, and documentation to verify conformance to Microsoft&#146;s responsible sourcing requirements. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>5.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Grievance Mechanism </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft&#146;s Global Human Rights Statement expresses our commitment to provide an
anonymous grievance reporting mechanism for our employees and other stakeholders who may be impacted by our operations. Microsoft&#146;s <FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Business Conduct Hotline</U></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> allows employees and others to anonymously ask compliance questions or report concerns regarding Microsoft&#146;s business operations, including our mineral sourcing policies or those of our suppliers. We investigate and,
where appropriate, take remedial action to address reported concerns. We also participate in industry efforts to develop grievance mechanisms for conflict minerals-related issues. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>B.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Identify and Assess Risk in the Supply Chain </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We took the following steps to identify and assess supplier conflict
mineral sourcing risk during this reporting year<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP>: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Using the Rule and SEC guidance, we generated a list of potential <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to receive Microsoft&#146;s annual CMRT survey. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We surveyed all potential <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers to determine the status of any 3TGs contained in devices manufactured during the 2017 reporting year by utilizing the RMAP-standard
CMRT and the services of a third-party solution provider. The survey followed OECD Guidance as tailored for Microsoft&#146;s role as a downstream company. Our survey included questions regarding the supplier&#146;s raw material due diligence
policies and procedures, its practices for engaging with its upstream suppliers, SORs from which its 3TGs were sourced, and the origins of 3TGs contained in the supplier&#146;s products. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We reviewed all supplier CMRT submissions to validate their completion and to identify contradictions or inconsistencies. We worked with our third-party solution provider to obtain updated responses from suppliers when
necessary. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We identified 200 active <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers for the 2017 reporting year. Of these suppliers, we received survey responses from 195 of those suppliers - a 98&nbsp;percent response
rate. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Microsoft completed its supplier conflict mineral sourcing data analysis for the 2017 reporting year on March&nbsp;31, 2018. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">7 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Figure 1. Response Rate for Active <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">In-scope</FONT> Suppliers (2013-2017 Reporting
Years) </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g594033st0011.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Response Rate for Surveyed Active <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">In-scope</FONT> Suppliers </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>III.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>DUE DILIGENCE DESIGN AND PERFORMANCE </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On the basis of our RCOI, we determined that 3TGs contained in our devices
may have originated in one or more Covered Country. Accordingly, we designed and performed due diligence on the source and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">chain-of-custody</FONT></FONT> of those 3TGs. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Due Diligence Design </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our 3TG due diligence process conformed to the third and fourth steps of the five-step OECD
Guidance. The first and second steps of the five-step OECD Guidance were addressed in Section II. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>B.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Due Diligence Performed </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>1.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Design and Implement a Strategy to Respond to Risks </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft required its suppliers to minimize the possible
sourcing of 3TGs from CAHRAs through contract requirements incorporating supplier specifications. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="13%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>a.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Microsoft Supplier Specifications - H00594, H00642 and H02050 </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft required identification of all materials,
including 3TGs, used in packaging and hardware products and parts on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">component-by-component</FONT></FONT> level through supplier specification H00594, Restricted Substances for
Hardware Products. H02050, Microsoft&#146;s Supplier Social and Environmental </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Accountability Manual, requires <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT>
suppliers to: </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">8 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Post a responsible sourcing policy, conforming to the OECD Guidance, on their website; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Exercise due diligence on the source and chain of custody of high risk raw materials, including 3TGs, contained in materials, components, or products supplied to Microsoft; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Identify, by name, each SOR that has processed or otherwise handled 3TGs contained in those materials, components, or products; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Encourage those SORs to participate in RMAP or an equivalent third-party responsible mineral audit scheme; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Confirm 3TGs in their supply chain are sourced from available SORs that are conformant with the RMAP or an equivalent independent private sector audit firm; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Notify Microsoft immediately if minerals used in the supplied materials, components, or products may contain 3TGs sourced from a CAHRA. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">H02050 requires Microsoft suppliers to impose these same requirements on their <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers and to assist <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> suppliers with appropriate training and support. To facilitate this process, Microsoft requires suppliers to utilize the CMRT provided by the RMAP and available at <FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>www.conflictfreesourcing.org</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL">. Suppliers must submit an annual CMRT and updated data upon request or when sourcing practices change. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="13%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>b.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Responsible Sourcing Program Manual Processes to Implement OECD Guidance </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft used the OECD Guidance to
review supplier CMRT data and identify potential red flags for the sourcing of raw materials. The red flags, which required additional supplier due diligence, included the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The minerals originated from or were transported via a CAHRA; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The minerals were claimed to have originated from a country that has limited known reserves for the mineral in question; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The minerals were claimed to have originated from a country in which minerals from a CAHRA are known to transit; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The company&#146;s suppliers or other known upstream companies had shareholder or other interests in companies that supply minerals or operate in one of the red flag locations of mineral origin and transit; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The company&#146;s suppliers or other known upstream companies were known to have sourced minerals from a red flag location of mineral origin and transit in the last 12 months. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">9 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft&#146;s program includes an escalation process that requires an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT>
supplier to find an alternative to a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-RMAP</FONT> conformant source of 3TGs for use in materials, components, or products supplied to Microsoft or risk termination as a Microsoft supplier. To date, we have not
encountered a RSRM issue with a supplier that has warranted contract termination. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft&#146;s internal Responsible Sourcing Program Manual requires
self-assessment, monitoring, and internal reporting of the RSRM program&#146;s progress and conformance. We utilize supplier survey updates, supplier communications, supplier social and environmental accountability audits, and new supplier briefings
to prevent the introduction of any new raw material sourcing risk to our supply chain. We leverage Microsoft&#146;s SEA Committee meetings with senior management to report findings and receive program guidance. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="13%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>c.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Industry and Partner Engagement </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft participated in or has been a member of several industry-wide
responsible mining and smelting initiatives: RMAP, ITRI&#146;s iTSCi program, PPA, IRMA, Pact, and ARM. We also conducted smelter outreach on behalf of the RMAP Smelter Engagement Team to further the RMAP program. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>2.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Carried Out Independent Third-Party Audit of Supply Chain Due Diligence </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As contemplated by OECD Guidance, our due
diligence program leveraged independent SOR audits. The audits conformed to the RMAP and other similar programs. Microsoft obtained SOR data from the RMAP Conformant Smelter List using <I>Reasonable Country of Origin Inquiry Data</I> for member
<I>MSFT</I>. The list identifies SORs that have undergone assessment through the RMAP or industry equivalent program, such as Responsible Jewellery Council (&#147;RJC&#148;) or London Bullion Market Association (&#147;LBMA&#148;). We used the list
to support certain statements contained in this CMR. Microsoft also participated in RMAPs Smelter Engagement Team during the 2017 reporting year. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>3.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Reported on Supply Chain Due Diligence </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have filed our CMR with the SEC and concurrently posted it on our <FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Responsible Sourcing website,</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"> which provides additional information about Microsoft&#146;s RSRM Program Results of our RSRM program are presented in Microsoft
Devices </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" COLOR="#1e5eff"><U>Social and Environmental Accountability Report for FY17</U></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL">. These disclosures meet the fifth step of the OECD Guidance. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>IV.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>SOR INFORMATION </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>3TG Processing Facilities </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft has made a reasonable good faith effort to collect and evaluate information
concerning 3TG SORs provided by our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers. The vast majority of our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers provided data at a company or divisional level. This level of
disclosure was expected given the multiple tiers of supply chain actors positioned between our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-scope</FONT> suppliers and 3TG SORs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our supplier survey data revealed 705 potential 3TG SORs in the Microsoft supply chain. We validated the data by removing duplicate SORs, reconciling multiple SOR names
for a single entity, and eliminating otherwise invalid SOR names. We then verified if the alleged SORs were active and participants in the RMAP audit program. We determined that 306 SORs met this criteria. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">10 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

Figure 2 categorizes the SORs by RMAP audit status and reporting year. Figure 2 indicates that the number of conformant SORs increased from 249 to 253. Figure 3 categorizes the SORs by 3TG mineral and audit status. A comparison from the 2016
reporting year showed that tungsten increased in the number and percentage of conformant and active smelters. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Figure 2. Identified SORs by CFSP Audit Status

the 2017 reporting year. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The RMAP classifies audit status in the following manner: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Conformant</U>: SOR has been audited and found to conform with the relevant audit protocols, including RMAP, LBMA, or RJC; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Outreach Required</U>: SOR is not yet active and outreach is needed by RMAP member companies to encourage SOR participation in RMAP; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Thailand</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Togo</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Uganda</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;United States of America</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Uzbekistan</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Vietnam</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Zimbabwe</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;United Arab Emirates</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8195;&#8202;Zambia</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Figure 8 provides a graphical presentation of the countries of origin for SORs identified in Microsoft&#146;s supply chain during the
2017 reporting year which processed 3TGs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Figure 8: <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Country-of-Origin</FONT></FONT>
Information for SORs Identified in Microsoft&#146;s Supply Chain </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g594033st0020.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">17 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For the identified conflict-free SORs for which minerals sourcing information is available from RMAP<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">4</SUP>: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">98 smelters, or 32&nbsp;percent of total smelters, processed recycled or scrap material; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">30 SORs, or 30&nbsp;percent of total smelters sourced from Covered Countries and were RMAP compliant. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>C.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>3TG Mines or Locations of Origin </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft obtained Reasonable Country of Origin data through our membership in
the RMAP using the <I>Reasonable Country of Origin Inquiry Data</I> for member <I>MSFT</I>. We used this data to determine the 3TG country of origin of SORs identified in Microsoft&#146;s supply chain. Microsoft supports the continued refinement and
expansion of the list of participating SORs in the RMAP audit program through our membership in RMAP. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We encouraged SORs to participate in the RMAP by contacting
all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-conformant</FONT> SORs identified in our supply chain each reporting year. We also required suppliers reporting <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-conformant</FONT> SORs to contact these SORs and request
them to join the CFSP. We actively supported outreach events to increase RMAP SOR coverage. We funded a third party to help educate SORs and prepare them for the audit process. We also offered to visit SORs to facilitate their participation in the
RMAP. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>V.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>IMPROVEMENTS </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This year&#146;s report documents our efforts to expand the number of verified conflict-free SORs in
our supply chain and demonstrates our progress. Microsoft&#146;s key 2017 reporting year accomplishments and improvements are detailed below: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increased number of RMAP-compliant SORs identified in Microsoft&#146;s supply chain from 249 to 253 due to enhanced supplier outreach, and maturation of RMAP; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Renewed and extended engagement with external organizations, such as Pact, IRMA, and ARM that are committed to advancing responsible sourcing on a global basis by developing mining standards and addressing issues such
as child labor in the mining industry. We partner closely with these organizations and leverage data and technology to bring about even greater change. With the further empowerment that digital technology can provide toward increased scope and
complexity, Microsoft and our partners can drive positive transformations in the mining sector. We believe this integrated approach is the most effective way to improve conditions for the people working in raw material supply chains;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Continued to increase Microsoft&#146;s level of engagement with suppliers and internal stakeholders by holding supplier forums, webinars, and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-person</FONT> trainings, and by providing
technical resources; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Fully integrated the RSRM program into our SEA audit process through the full use of </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft&#146;s Audit Management System; </P>
<P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">4</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All numbers include both direct and indirect sourcing. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">18 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Ensured commitment to transparency by publishing Microsoft&#146;s SEA supplier manual, which includes Responsible Sourcing of Raw Material Requirements; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Strengthened internal partnerships to identify raw material risk at an early product development stage. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>VI.</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>FUTURE ACTIONS </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Microsoft is committed to the responsible sourcing of raw materials used in our hardware products
in support of human rights, labor, health and safety, environmental protection, and business. We will continue to advance implementation of our RSRM policy in our supply chain. The policy consists of supply chain identification and risk assessment,
standardized requirements and verification, capability building, transparency, and partnerships. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We will continue to encourage SORs to participate in the RMAP and
expand our knowledge about 3TGs in our supply chain. Our ability to identify, assess, and mitigate risks associated with our raw materials sourcing will improve with ongoing due diligence efforts &#150; with both our direct and <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">sub-tier</FONT> partners. Consistent with our commitments, we intend to take the following steps to improve our responsible sourcing of raw materials due diligence efforts: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Enhance our use of digital technology to improve supply chain information and risk mitigation; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increase use of external data sources to proactively identify raw material risk in CAHRAs; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Continue our active participation in the RMAP Smelter Engagement Team to bring <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-</FONT> conformant SORs into the CFSP; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Further our engagement with organizations like IRMA, ARM, and Pact to establish global responsible sourcing standards and support programs in the mineral supply chain. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">19 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
